459
00:24:58,940 --> 00:25:02,220
But basically, I mean, that's what it comes down to, right?

460
00:25:02,220 --> 00:25:05,721
Is everything about this tool is about empowering us,

461
00:25:05,721 --> 00:25:08,802
as designers and artists, to do our job

462
00:25:08,802 --> 00:25:10,502
that much faster than we normally could.

463
00:25:10,502 --> 00:25:13,623
And that's why all the systems are built that way.

464
00:25:13,623 --> 00:25:17,043
And honestly, working in it is a dream.

465
00:25:17,043 --> 00:25:20,224
I worked in other editors before, in school,

466
00:25:20,224 --> 00:25:21,844
for fun, whatever.

467
00:25:21,844 --> 00:25:25,205
But, to be fair, it just doesn't compare at all

468
00:25:25,205 --> 00:25:27,625
to the power that we have with UBART framework.

469
00:25:57,530 --> 00:26:00,230
I'm very sorry.

470
00:26:00,230 --> 00:26:00,710
I hope so.

471
00:26:00,710 --> 00:26:03,531
On my first time too, what are the chances?

