00:55:42,497 --> 00:55:42,617
Okay.

1101
00:55:42,617 --> 00:55:44,159
I mean, pretty much.

1102
00:55:44,159 --> 00:55:48,923
I mean, are there any things that you thought were particularly a good level that...

1103
00:55:49,527 --> 00:55:52,748
they weren't into and you had to make your case for more or?

1104
00:55:52,748 --> 00:55:53,028
Of course.

1105
00:55:53,028 --> 00:55:53,108
Yeah.

1106
00:55:53,108 --> 00:55:54,909
But I mean that's what it comes down to, right?

1107
00:55:54,909 --> 00:55:55,869
It's about convincing people.

1108
00:55:55,869 --> 00:55:58,609
That's what I've been talking about with the prototyping process and everything.

1109
00:55:58,609 --> 00:56:01,670
It needs to be clear to convince somebody that this is a good idea.

1110
00:56:01,670 --> 00:56:05,551
And I've seen a lot of people that go in with a half-baked proposal.

1111
00:56:05,551 --> 00:56:07,892
They say, oh look, it's a red square on the floor.

1112
00:56:07,892 --> 00:56:08,632
It's a button.

1113
00:56:08,632 --> 00:56:09,392
It's like, oh, okay.

1114
00:56:09,992 --> 00:56:10,953
I guess, I trust you."

1115
00:56:10,953 --> 00:56:14,454
And they jump and it doesn't do anything except open a door and stuff and it doesn't make

1116
00:56:14,454 --> 00:56:14,934
sense.

1117
00:56:14,934 --> 00:56:18,175
But when you make it look like what it's supposed to be, feel like what it's supposed to be,

1118
00:56:18,175 --> 00:56:22,417
and then you show it in a multitude of different situations, then it's very clear for them

1119
00:56:22,417 --> 00:56:27,339
whether or not they just hate the idea or they can't deny that it's actually quite cool.

1120
00:56:27,639 --> 00:56:30,021
So when it comes to reviewing levels and things like that,

1121
00:56:30,021 --> 00:56:32,523
it's just that the level design lead comes, sits down with you,

1122
00:56:32,523 --> 00:56:34,784
and says, this is good, this is not,

1123
00:56:34,784 --> 00:56:35,885
try to go more in this direction.

1124
00:56:35,885 --> 00:56:38,607
And if you really disagree, you can take one more chance

1125
00:56:38,607 --> 00:56:39,808
to try to prove it to him.

1126
00:56:39,808 --> 00:56:42,410
But honestly, that's the whole part about failing and moving on.

1127
00:56:42,410 --> 00:56:44,731
Nothing is sacred. Just trash it and move on.

1128
00:56:44,731 --> 00:56:46,793
You can make something better in five minutes anyway.

1129
00:56:46,793 --> 00:56:47,033
Thank you.

1130
00:56:47,033 --> 00:56:51,516
I'm a little curious about the development

