1132
00:56:57,694 --> 00:57:00,958
what led up to it, and how long was it in development

1133
00:57:00,958 --> 00:57:01,939
before it was used?

1134
00:57:01,939 --> 00:57:06,704
And when you add key features and stuff,

1135
00:57:06,704 --> 00:57:07,905
how long does that typically take?

1136
00:57:08,981 --> 00:57:12,322
Well, the engine was originally created by the creative director,

1137
00:57:12,322 --> 00:57:16,584
Michel Ancel, and a small team of, I believe, five senior programmers.

1138
00:57:16,584 --> 00:57:18,265
The initial version, of course.

1139
00:57:18,265 --> 00:57:20,946
I mean, then we ramped up to a few more engineers

1140
00:57:20,946 --> 00:57:22,327
as the process went on.

1141
00:57:22,327 --> 00:57:23,727
We were building the game itself.

1142
00:57:23,727 --> 00:57:25,848
But it was a small team developing the tools for that.

1143
00:57:25,848 --> 00:57:30,791
And then the team started to ramp up maybe a year later, I believe.

1144
00:57:30,791 --> 00:57:33,952
And we started to actually go into production on Rayman Origins.

1145
00:57:33,952 --> 00:57:36,993
And it's just been in constant update status ever since.

1146
00:57:37,613 --> 00:57:40,194
But when it came to something like the lighting engine,

1147
00:57:40,194 --> 00:57:42,815
the new update for the lighting system,

1148
00:57:42,815 --> 00:57:43,595
it took quite a while.

1149
00:57:43,595 --> 00:57:46,076
Like, I believe, if I remember correctly,

1150
00:57:46,076 --> 00:57:47,776
maybe a month or two

1151
00:57:47,776 --> 00:57:50,217
to wait to get that thing actually working.

1152
00:57:50,217 --> 00:57:52,798
But it's a heavier system, so it takes more time.

1153
00:57:52,798 --> 00:57:54,738
But some engine improvements,

1154
00:57:54,738 --> 00:57:57,079
they don't take any time at all.

1155
00:57:57,079 --> 00:57:59,400
They take like maybe one, two, three days tops,

1156
00:57:59,400 --> 00:58:01,140
depending on what it is.

1157
00:58:01,140 --> 00:58:01,440
Thank you.

1158
00:58:01,440 --> 00:58:01,500
Yep.

